Real Madrid have confirmed that vice-captain, Marcelo, has been diagnosed with a muscular injury ahead of their La Liga fixture against Espanyol on Saturday afternoon at the Santiago Bernabeu. Zinedine Zidane’s side made this known in a statement on the club’s official website on Thursday. The statement reads: “Following by tests carried out on our player, Marcelo, by the Real Madrid medical department. “He has been diagnosed with a muscular injury in his left soleus. His recovery will continue to be assessed.” Real Madrid head to the game following a 2-1 victory over Alaves in the La Liga encounter last weekend. The kick-off for the match is 1pm Nigerian time. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.